data.chText: 参议院（美国、澳大利亚、加拿大、法国等国家的两个立法机构之一；美国许多州议会也设有参议院）
data.enText: one of the two groups of elected politicians who make laws in some countries, for example in the US, Australia, Canada and France. The Senate is smaller than the other group but higher in rank. Many state parliaments in the US also have a Senate.

data.chText: （某些国家的）大学理事会，大学评议会
data.enText: (in some countries) the group of people who control a university
(in ancient Rome) the most important council of the government; the building where the council met

simple_means.memory_skill: sen 老 + ate 表职位 → 资格老的人组成的领导班子 → 参议院，上院

means: 参议院(美国、澳大利亚、加拿大、法国等国家的两个立法机构之一，美国许多州议会也设有参议院)

value.def: The Senate is the smaller and more important of the two parts of the parliament in some countries, for example the United States and Australia.

example.ex: The Senate is expected to pass the bill shortly.
example.tran: 预计参议院不久就会通过此议案。

value.tran: (美国、澳大利亚等国议会的)参议院

value.def: Senate or the Senate is the governing council at some universities.

example.ex: By the time I was Vice Chancellor, Senate had become a much larger and a much more democratic body...
example.tran: 到了我当校长的时候，大学评议会的人员规模已显著扩大，也变得更加民主了。

example.ex: The new bill would remove student representation from the university Senate.
example.tran: 新议案将取消大学评议会中的学生代表。

value.tran: （某些大学的）大学理事会，大学评议会

partsOfSpeech.dec: sen 老 + ate 表职位 → 资格老的人组成的领导班子 → 参议院，上院
sen 老 + ator 表人 → 参议员
senator 参议员 + ial 具有…的，属于…的 → 参议员的
sen 老 + ile 易于…的 → 衰老的
sen 老 + ior 较…的 → 年长的
senior 年长的 + ity 具备某种性质，状况 → 年长
